cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.FL, cs.DS 

This paper presents a novel resource analysis for logic programs using abstract interpretation and sized types. The paper focuses on the analysis of logic programs, which falls under the programming languages (cs.PL) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of abstract interpretation, which is a technique commonly used in the formal methods (cs.LO) sub-category. The paper also discusses the integration of the analysis into the Ciao preprocessor, which is a software engineering (cs.SE) topic. The paper also discusses the comparison of the analysis to state-of-the-art systems, which is a topic in the formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories.
